      • fetchedDoc

        private void fetchedDoc()
        This method find and fetches data from database based on the Stitch user's Id, and Plant Collection.

        It checks for null and successful retrieval of the document from the database. If that is successful then it sets up the Plant Profile with that information. Otherwise display error.

      • setupPlantProfile

        private void setupPlantProfile(org.bson.Document profile)
        Parameters:
        profile - Document fetched by the system corresponding to the user profile. Takes as a parameter the Fetched Document from the Plant profile, if any. then the document feeds all the parameters to a Plant Profile, which is later on used to feed all the Layout's widgets.

      • saveNameAndTime

        private void saveNameAndTime()
        Method responsible for saving name and data of plant, changed by the user.

        It gets data from Plant Profile Collection, if task is successful it continues by checking the bitmap, in case tht is successful it updates picture and proceed to check for empty or invalid input for name and date. If both are not empty and the date is valid, it proceeds by updating the data.

      • saveChanges

        private void saveChanges()
        Method responsible for saving minimum and maximum conditions of plant, changed by the user.

        This method takes input for minimum and maximum of all our 3 measurements: Humidity, Temperature and Sunlight. After the user thinks that the input for the measurements are fine he can proceed to update them.

        He is displayed an dialogue with the "Yes" and "No", where he can select and update the values if the minimum and maximum are not less or more then the applicable for each field. If that's appropriate he updates the values, if not he is requested to change them, because he gets appropriate errors.
